1. By inſtance of ſome ſpeciall ſinnes; againſt which, the Curſe is particularly threatened. Many other foule Enormities there were in the Iewiſh State at this time; as, Marriage of ſtrange Wives, unlawfull and cruell Divorces of their Wives,
                     Molachie per tutum. Sabbath-breaking, and open contempt of Gods Worſhip;
                     Nehem. 5. Crueltie and unmercifulneſſe towards their poore Brethren, &c. but two onely are named, though foule and groſſe ones.

